The paper discusses a methodology for compressive image recovery using denoising-based approximate message passing (D-AMP) and vector approximate message passing (VAMP) algorithms. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT) for the discussion of message passing algorithms, Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) for the application to image recovery, Machine Learning (cs.LG) for the use of sophisticated denoisers, Multimedia (cs.MM) for the discussion of image processing, and Signal Processing (cs.SP) for the use of signal processing techniques.
